  "title": "Introduction to the History of Burmese Cuisine",
  "lessonText": "Burmese cuisine reflects a rich tapestry of cultural influences and historical events.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- Influenced by neighboring countries: India, China, Thailand.\n- Historical trade routes introduced diverse ingredients.\n- Colonial period brought new cooking techniques and flavors.\n- Traditional dishes often reflect local customs and celebrations."
  }
